l<\/nobr> or butter to the cooking water to reduce frothing.","Pasta that is cooked al dente is tender but still firm to the bite.","The heat of the cooked pasta will partially cook and thicken the egg, so it is important the pasta is still hot when adding the egg mixture to the serving bowl.","To ensure eggs do not overcook and sauce is creamy, rinse the mixing bowl in cold water to cool it off, after draining the spaghetti, before adding eggs."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","40m","4 portions"]}